question
Write a function createReverseArray that takes a non-negative integer n as an argument and returns an array containing integers
from n to 0: [n, n-1, ..., 3, 2, 1, 0].
Example:
createReverseArray (5) should return [5, 4, 3, 2, 1, 0];
createReverseArray (2) should return [2, 1, 0];
createReverseArray (1) should return [1, 0];
createReverseArray (0) must return [0]


solution:

function createReverseArray(n){
  let arr = [];
    for(let i = n; i >= 0; i--){
      arr.push(i);
      }
      return arr;
}
